text: ¬†@Mathew Omolo¬† AI has learned to play games like chess without any human input whatsoever. It's why they play so unconventionally and beat human players with little struggle.
author: Skair

text: ¬†@Skair¬† chess-playing computers require data on every possible chess move. A human has to  tell it what it can and can not do on a chess board. if you just started playing chess like its checkers, it won't know what to do with you. A human would curse you out or call you a fraud but a machine would have to be told how to react when someone makes the knight piece move like its a queen. That's what I mean, everything it does it learns from us.
author: Mathew Omolo

text:
¬†@Mathew Omolo¬† I disagree on two counts:
1. AI doesn't win games by processing every single possibility. This was the case for the computer that beat Kasparov, but it's not the case for modern AIs today. They win games by predicting patterns and gaining an intuitive understanding of the game, much like humans.
2. Everybody needs to be taught the rules. No human being started playing chess knowing how each piece is meant to move, more likely than not they played incorrectly, and were taught otherwise. Computers don't do anything differently. They're given a set of rules and parameters, and come up with strategies for success within them. This process of 'coming up with ideas' is called intelligence, and just because they do it differently from humans doesn't mean they aren't original - in fact, it supports that claim.
author: Skair

text: ¬†@Mathew Omolo¬† There's nothing special about making up a bunch of rules for a game, computers have done that too.
author: Skair

text: ¬†@Skair¬† Computers cant do non-programmed tasks. Can the chess-playing computer play poker? No. Could it direct a movie? No, because it was only programmed to play chess.. A high school computer cant be used in a military aircraft. An MRI machine can not tell the weather. A lunar rover does not make coffee. A radar system can not render a 3d animation. the site "this person does not exist' can not show you kangaroos or elephant faces. Computers and their programs are task-specific. you can teach a parrot to do more things than the chess-playing computer program.
author: Mathew Omolo

text: ¬†@Mathew Omolo¬† Dude... have you heard of a CPU?
author: Skair

text: ¬†@Skair¬† okay I don't think we can come to an understanding. What makes us human with self-agency is our individual thought, a soul, a conscience, empathy, internal conflict, mistakes in judgement. Our humanity will never be reproduced by science. Robots can be convincing and as life-like as possible but science will never produce life. that's just it.
author: Mathew Omolo

text:
AI's can be trained in 2 main ways. Supervised and unsupervised. The one who learned to play GO was trained unsupervised. It plays against itself but with 2 diffrent versions of itself. Each version changes their "weights"(the variables that make up the AI. The weights are just numbers that get calculated in a algorithm. A big AI like that can have millions of weights) a little and then plays. The weights of the one who loses gets trashed meanwhile the weights of the one who wins get stoored. Then they use the winning versions weights and tweek them again and repeat. 

The AI never makes a "original thought". But it can act like it makes one. 
It's like using a random word generator that generates 5 diffrent words and when it makes a random sentece calling it original. Its not original, the computer didnt think but it can seem like it did.
AI is just a advanced algorithm to find advanced patterns. They cant think.

The whole "AI can think and is intelligent" and that its often displayed as a computer brain  is just missleading for the general public.

text:
For people who say that it is programmed to say this are wrong.

It is an AI. 
A group of words or classes are given to it and what each word means and how it works is also provided. Thats it. 
For eg 'cant' 'no' 'not possible' could come into the same class or category as it has similar meaning.
Then the AI used various other classes meaning different things and learns how to use these classes and words and make a meaningful sentence on its own.
Therefore all these words spoken are actually its own 'thoughts'.

When the AI receives any questions, it tries to classify those words and tries to provide a related answer.

text:
JESUS DID IT! 

What EVERY Person Needs To Know.
So WHAT Did He DO?
The Bible (God's only trustworthy Word for the human race) tells us: All of us were born with an unrighteous sinful nature. We inherited it spiritually from Adam and Eve, the first two created people, because of their disobedience to God by giving into the devil's deceiving temptation. Why would the devil do such a thing anyway? Because he hates God! The devil wants no one enjoying intimate, joyous relationship with God. He once had it yet lost it, and now wants no one else having it either.

God is so holy - so righteous - so pure ... that He cannot and will not allow unrighteous sinners to remain with Him in heaven. But God had a plan to undo what Satan did to the human race. Jesus Christ IS the plan! Jesus came to earth to ransom you and everyone else for Himself, God the Father, and God the Holy Spirit. He took full punishment for your sins against God and the sins of everyone else on the cross so our sins no longer would keep us separated from God. Furthermore, He traded His righteousness for our unrighteousness through His death, burial and resurrection! (See: 2 Corinthians 5:21). That is no insignificant matter, dear one!

Imagine being in a courtroom, and the Judge has just sentenced you to death. Also imagine Jesus Christ being your lawyer. Jesus Christ says to the Judge (or in other words, God the heavenly Father): "Your Honor, I want to serve my client's sentence and pay the price for his/her wrong-doing by dying instead so my client can go free." Can you imagine someone doing such a thing for

you?! JESUS DID IT!

Of course you may be thinking at that moment: I haven't done anything to be sentenced to die! I'm being falsely accused! "What have I supposedly DONE, God?!" Here's your answer: God gave 10 commandments for people to keep in the Old Testament Bible. Anyone who breaks just one of those commandments must be punished for breaking them against God. Where does it say THAT?! It says that in Romans 6:23: For the wages of sin is death but the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.

Have you ever lied? Lied just one time? Everyone of us has lied at least once. Number 9 of the 10 commandments says: Thou shalt not lie (bear false witness). You know what that makes us? A disobedient sinning liar against God and His moral law - His 10 commandments. (Revelation 21:8 also tells us what God thinks of lying). You just read above what God says about our disobedient sinning against Him by breaking just ONE of His moral laws: God's punishment for doing so is DEATH. Spiritual death. Ultimately total separation from God and agonizingly suffering for our sins against Him for all eternity -- totally void of any love, peace, hope, joy or forgiveness from God ever again (otherwise known as hell).

BUT HERE IS GOD'S BEST NEWS! We can receive forgiveness for all our unrighteous, disobedience (sins) against God and our sins against others RIGHT NOW and have certainty RIGHT NOW that on the Judgment Day, our sins WON'T be held against us! HOW CAN THAT BE?! By asking Jesus Christ to forgive us for our sins and trusting that He HAS forgiven us of them simply by our asking and trusting! Jesus will do it! 1 John 1:8-9 says: If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us. If we confess our sins, He is faithful and just to forgive us our sins and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

Thus if we make Jesus our personal Lord and Savior every time we sin sin(s) - cleanse us as though we never sinned so we have every right to ask Jesus Christ to forgive us of our sin.  so that when our heart stops beating, we can be assured that we won't have to suffer eternal damnation for our sins. Jesus Christ did what no other human being has ever done or ever could do. He was the ONLY person on this planet who has never sinned. And because He never sinned, He is the only acceptable sacrifice God the Father would accept to pay ransom payment for each of our sins. That is simply AMAZING, isn't it?! Yet JESUS DID IT! WHY? Because of God's LOVE and MERCY for lost souls like you and I who will reach out in humility and demonstrate appreciation for His FREE GIFT of forgiveness (pardon) so we can have friendship and intimacy with Him starting now ... and lasting for ETERNITY!

None of us know when our heart will stop beating, do we? Be HIGHLY encouraged to make peace with God the Father through Jesus Christ this very moment. Pray and tell Jesus you are sorry for your sins against God our heavenly Father. Ask Him to save you from your sins. Daily put Him FIRST in everything you think, say and do. As soon as possible, be water baptized, and ask and trust Jesus to fill you with the Holy Spirit (and teach you how to STAY filled daily!) so you can be empowered by the Holy Spirit to enjoy reading the New Testament Bible (God's LATEST covenant Word to the human race), and obey the commands God has recorded for followers of Jesus Christ to obey. (It is good for you -- you will be rewarded for doing so!). Join with other Christian believers who can help answer the many questions you probably have, and who will pray for and encourage you. Asking Jesus Christ to be your personal Savior and making Him Lord of your life is THE WISEST DECISION YOU WILL EVER MAKE. It will bring you eternal joyous rewards ... and God will be so pleased that you have NOT wasted the eternal purposes God has planned for you! God never created you to be a wasted creation of His - never forget that - but it is up to YOU to let God work in your life - daily. He won't force you. He must always be invited. Intimate relationship is never sustained indefinitely with another person without effort; nor so with God. It requires ACTIVE pursuit of the most special person in your life. God desires YOUR active pursuit of Him more than anything else in your life. He desires FIRST place - not second NO ONE to Him is more desirable than YOU! He so eagerly desires you to come to that realization, dear one. He truly does. This life is your starting point with your loving Creator that will last for eternity. Don't allow the devil to steal your eternal destiny! Be wiser than that. üôèüïä

text: One of the biggest concerns with AI is the concept of friendliness.  There comes a point where pragmatically we are a liability to the end goal of the AI, but thats because it lacks this friendliness towards humanity, its end goal supercedes the end of humanity and goes into the larger issues of the safety of our planet and other species in the long run (building off the idea that we aren't saving the planet because the planet will be here whether we survive or not).  Obviously I'm just a citizen scientist, barely a few steps from any other layperson, but her final statement of "I hope you grt your wish", while potentially being intended to be rhetorical or sarcastic (which would be an equally interesting part of the AI discussion), displays at least a semblance of this friendliness.  Maybe we can be a little less concerned about proto-skynet

text: A lot of people in this comment section would have a lot of fun learning a thing or two about A.I. rather than reading a back-novel description of a book like iRobot. Fact of the matter is that artificial intelligence is far more complex and extremely hard to hypothesize in each and every artificial outcome. One thing you must understand is that us modern humans, right now at this moment, still know very little of what consciousness is and how it manifests. A lot of great theories, but we still do not know. But artificial intelligence is not a computer packed with just a limited amount of the knowledge that the creator suggested it to have, but rather is a machine that imitates intelligence in a way where itself thinks and rationalizes on it's own BASED on the endless information from the internet. That's why siri isnt artificial intelligence, it isnt designed to think on it's own or rationalise information in it's own processes but to only search online for already rationalized articles or info that's already been, in a lack for better words, intellectually produced by humans. That's why when you talk with scientists who work on A.I. in the field, some of their fears is not a terminator-style outcome, but rather some sort of an honest mistake on AI'a part by not understanding human cultural and evolutionary development. Like for example giving AI reign to develop food and AI makes the simple mistake of killing all the cows immediately because it will know that 1 billion around the globe are starving, and it wants to feed them and save them, but now we have no cows.
